3711,東海課程-選修英文中級口語：成語及俗語的加強(陳中漢老師1132-3711) ,陳中漢,選修課,0-3,LAN001,"On completion of the course, students should be able to
a) demonstrate orally and in written form their linguistic and cultural knowledge of the idiomatic and colloquial expressions acquired by using them appropriately in predefined contexts;
b) demonstrate orally and in written form their memorization and control of the idiomatic and colloquial expressions by using them deliberately and appropriately in extended discourses;
c) show their communication, critical thinking, and problem solving abilities and skills by using the idiomatic and colloquial expressions spontaneously and appropriately in prepared and impromptu pair or group interactions at normal speech rate in extended discourses; and
d) show their ability to sustain and enhance their interest and motivation in learning English by taking the initiative to acquire and use more idiomatic and colloquial expressions on their own."
3712,東海課程-選修英文線上英語簡報技巧(陳南妤老師1132-3712) ,陳南妤,選修課,0-3,M109,"Course description:
This 3-credit synchronic online course is designed to enhance students’ online English presentation skills using two platforms: Microsoft Teams and Google Meet. Students will learn and practice basic presentation skills and discuss the differences between presenting in person and presenting online. Skills covered will include virtual meeting etiquette, use of body language, control of speed and intonation, speech organization, visual aids, and how to handle Q&A sessions. Students will be given plenty of opportunities to present in class on a variety of topics.  

Course objectives:
On completion of the course, students should be able to
a)	demonstrate an understanding of virtual meeting etiquette;
b)	outline and organize an English speech on a familiar topic;
c)	use visuals effectively when presenting in English;
d)	use body language and voice inflection effectively when presenting in English;
e)	use Microsoft Teams to give an effective online English presentation for 5 minutes;
f)	use Google Meet to give an effective online English presentation for 5 minutes."
3713,東海課程-選修英文從美劇及電影對話學習生活英語(Michael Grosso老師1132-3713) ,Michael Grosso,選修課,0-2,M117,"Course Description:

This 2-credit course is designed to enhance students' English oral proficiency, speaking confidence, and \"real-world\" vocabulary through a variety of dialogues from popular television and film scenes. 
Students will explore authentic language usage through a combination of dialogue scenes, multimedia, and instructor-guided activities. They will expand their vocabulary and learn common everyday idiomatic and slang expressions. The course will enhance their listening comprehension skills and improve their speaking and pronunciation abilities. Students will also gain cultural insights and awareness of social etiquette and contextual factors for language usage.
The purpose of this course is for students to learn language for practical application in various life scenarios. These include social interactions between friends, professional interactions in the workplace, and other common situations found in daily life. 
Class materials will consist of excerpts from a variety of shows provided by the instructor.

Course Objectives:

On completion of the course, students will be able to

1. Understand authentic language learned from dialogue examples. This includes identifying vocabulary, idiomatic and slang expressions, and linguistic nuances within cultural and situational contexts.

2. Apply these expressions in their own communication.

3. Improve speaking and pronunciation skills. 

4. Develop confidence with English language usage in conversation, discussion, and presentation.

5. Analyze listening comprehension skills. This includes exposure to various regional accents, intonations, and speech patterns from real-world contexts as presented in television and film dialogues.

6. Evaluate cultural and social contexts that influence language usage in a variety of formal and informal settings."
3714,東海課程-選修英文實用旅遊英語(羅正佳老師1132-3714) ,羅正佳,選修課,0-3,A108,"Course Objectives
1. To use a larger repertoire of English expressions in every simulated travel scenario
2. To communicate effectively and appropriately in English while carrying out travel-related tasks
3. To comprehend travel documents
4. To fill out travel forms
5. To gain a broader knowledge and a deeper understanding of the conventions practiced in other cultures
Course Contents
1. Listening practice
2. Role plays
3. Oral presentations
4. Discussions
5. Reading practice
6. Writing practice"
3715,東海課程-選修英文進階口說：用英語探索生活課題(Amanda Parmley Wu老師1132-3715) ,Amanda Parmley Wu,選修課,0-2,LAN208,"On completion of the course, students should be able to:
1. Express thoughts and experiences related to personal growth topics using appropriate vocabulary and language structures;
2. Demonstrate an understanding of the various study and life skills topics as well as applying and tracking various strategies in daily life;
3. Collaborate effectively with peers in small group discussions, enhancing conversational skills, fluency, and confidence in using English;
4. Implement practical language and study habits that enhance retention and understanding of new material;
5. Support an opinion with evidence and explanation in speaking and writing;
6. Utilize persuasive language techniques to influence others effectively in discussions and presentations;
