The primary focus is on listening, speaking, and conversation. Students will have numerous opportunities to speak English in the class. Through small group and class-wide discussions, their listening comprehension will be strengthened. Students will express ideas, opinions, and connect personal experiences and knowledge to daily topics. In addition, reading and listening materials will aid students in critical thinking and help them develop organizing of ideas and reasoning skills."
4115,東海課程-大二英文大二英文：日常溝通(Michael Grosso老師1132-4115) ,Michael Grosso,必修課,0-2,PG303,"Learn English Expression through Short Poems

從詩歌學英文表達

藉由閱讀各種題材的短詩及歌詞，學生學習常用英文詞彙、增進基礎英文聽說讀寫技能、加強英語發音及表達能力，並且透過理解及討論短詩及歌詞的內容及意涵，練習表達個人原創的想法、啟發創造力。

Students will read a variety of short poems and lyrics as authentic language texts in order to build a knowledge of expressive English vocabulary; develop basic language skills (i.e. reading, writing, listening and speaking); improve tools for daily expression, such as pronunciation while speaking about poetry, building new vocabulary, learning techniques found in poetry and get experience expressing creative individual voice. Students will also engage in active discussion and attempt to use English to express opinions about poetry and its meaning."
4116,東海課程-大二英文大二英文：多元文化(吳舜華老師1132-4116) ,吳舜華,必修課,0-2,PG202,"Contents:  
【主題：當旅遊遇上文化】
本課程分成兩大類型。期中前上課方式以任務型導向，每周都以不同的文化元素主題來探討，同時對於學習評量，我們也將跳脫傳統的小考模式，改以講義學習，口語的演練和益智遊戲來評分。期中之後的課程為單一國深入探討，課程多以旅行中如何享受異國文化也要避免不必要的尷尬和衝突來進行。老師在課程最後會分享旅遊中有趣的小故事。讓大家更能體會，懂文化、知文化、說文化、才能讓你國際化。

Theme of Course: When Travel Meets Culture 
This course is designed into two parts. The first part is task-based. Students will learn different cultural knowledge and experience them through a variety of activities, role-plays, worksheets and handouts instead of quizzes and tests. The second part is about travel and cultures. Students will be given more insight into a number of countries and, meanwhile, the instructor will give some tips on avoiding any awkward, disrespectful or impolite occurrences while traveling. She will also share some interesting real-life stories and anecdotes during those cross-cultural interactions."
4117,東海課程-大二英文大二英文：多元文化(吳文祺老師1132-4117) ,吳文祺,必修課,0-2,PG302,"On completion of the course, students should be able to
1) provide real-life examples of social and cultural diversity; 
2) demonstrate their multicultural awareness and appreciation; 
3) use idiomatic expressions acquired in the course; and 
4) express their opinions on diversity issues more confidently.
Contents:
課程特點：
每週介紹不同的文化主題，從打招呼，肢體語言，餐飲文化，旅遊會展，到網路社群應用，學生可以透過聽力練習與閱讀段落主題，來體驗東西方文化包含數十個國家不同的習俗，禮儀，與常規。課堂教材除了指定用書之外，老師也會融入網路媒體與數位頻道或是歐美影集引起學習興趣與討論，或是介紹國際文化新聞以提高學生的國際關注力。
Module Features:
    Different topics would be introduced every week ranging from a variety of ways of greetings, body language (gestures), tourism and MICE industry to social media. Students can enhance their listening and reading by focusing on acquired materials including textbooks, online resources and videos. Not only can students experience difference cultures, customs and etiquettes by accessing those media, but also raise cultural awareness by discussing those topics with peers."
4118,東海課程-大二英文大二英文：自我表達技巧(Jonathan Brian Walter Hayes老師1132-4118) ,Jonathan Brian Walter Hayes,必修課,0-2,PG103,"[媒體,科技與簡報]
[Virtual Speech and Presentation]
Contents: This course is designed for students who wish to improve their speaking and presentation skills with a focus on using modern technology and methods for speech and presentation. There will be a “virtual” aspect to the classroom and activities, where students will use video, digital software, applications, and other innovative ways to produce and enhance their speeches and presentations.
Course Objectives:
On completion of the course, students should be able to
1) deliver a variety of formal and informal presentations in English;
2) present ideas clearly with emphasis on effective use of verbal and nonverbal communication skills;
3) demonstrate critical thinking skills in daily life communication, both as a speaker and as a listener; and
4) express their ideas in English more confidently."
4119,東海課程-大二英文大二英文：自我表達技巧(余詩芸老師1132-4119) ,余詩芸,必修課,0-2,M109,"Theme of this course: Functional and Situational Self-expression 
Course Description
This semester-long course is designed to help students develop various communication skills they need to speak clearly, effectively, and confidently. Students are expected to participate in collaborative tasks and group discussions in class.

語境的自我表達
這門為期一學期的課主要是在幫助學生培養清晰、有效和自信地說話所需的各種表達溝通技巧。學生透過在課堂上討論和密集的練習及上課互動來提昇學生的英語溝通以及表達能力。"
4120,東海課程-大二英文大二英文：職涯與專業(林靜美老師1132-4120) ,林靜美,必修課,0-2,LAN014-1,"「職涯規劃超前佈署」
本課程提供職場所需的語言技巧與知識，以有效促進學生英文溝通能力，讓學習者在職場的英語能力表現更上一層樓。


 「English for Career Development」

Offering activities based on the real workplace and everyday communication at work for students"
4121,東海課程-大二英文大二英文：日常溝通(Henry Westheim老師1132-4121) ,Henry Westheim,必修課,0-2,LAN010,"Everyday English (日常英語)

This course is designed for students who want to improve their fluency, accuracy and confidence using English in informal daily conversations.

The primary focus is on listening, speaking, and conversation. Students will have numerous opportunities to speak English in the class. Through small group and class-wide discussions, their listening comprehension will be strengthened. Students will express ideas, opinions, and connect personal experiences and knowledge to daily topics. In addition, reading and listening materials will aid students in critical thinking and help them develop organizing of ideas and reasoning skills."
4122,東海課程-大二英文大二英文：日常溝通(陳永豪老師1132-4122) ,陳永豪,必修課,0-2,LAN011,"【英語玩家】
喜歡玩遊戲嗎？可曾想過人活著就像是在玩一場史詩級的角色扮演遊戲呢？想要玩好名為「人生」的遊戲需要好幾項技能，語言是其中一項。能多說一種除了母語以外的語言就能無限強化自己在這個遊戲裡的角色，只要想學，隨時都可以開始。在這門課裡，大家都是「英語」玩家。玩家們可以透過另一種語言看世界，吸收、討論、呈現關於這個世界的種種，玩透這世界。一起以駕馭英語為目標邁進吧！

[English Player One]
Do you like games? Have you ever thought that this life you are living right now is a huge RPG world? It actually is! One of the ways to get the most out of this game/world/life is to equip yourself with another language. Being able to speak another language other than your mother tongue is an ability, a skill, a talent, and, for some people, even a blessing. However, learning a new language is always possible as long as you make up your mind to start. So, in this course, you will use the English language to learn more about how you, as an \"English\" player, can see the world from a different point of view and have more fun living in it."
4123,東海課程-大二英文大二英文：多元文化(廖晨甯老師1132-4123) ,廖晨甯,必修課,0-2,LAN014,"Interpersonal Communication across Cultures:
The objective of this course is to promote students' cultural awareness and understanding of cultural diversity. In addition, students can benefit from developing communicative competence on the basis of intercultural awareness. By identifying and appreciating one’s own culture and respecting differences from others through reading, listening and speaking activities in English, students will not only learn cultural knowledge in a global context, but will also learn to reflect and cope with some of the project-based communication scenarios.

跨文化溝通:
本課程旨在啟發文化多樣性與多元文化意識，同時通過這種跨文化理解，進一步培養學生跨文化英語溝通能力。課程將透過閱讀、聽力和口說練習活動，來增進學生對自身及不同文化之識別、欣賞和尊重的態度，以全球化時代的視角，運用反思及創意進行專題式成果報告，學習並體現跨文化溝通技能。"
4124,東海課程-大二英文大二英文：多元文化(陳美君老師1132-4124) ,陳美君,必修課,0-2,A108,"Contents:  
【主題：讀文化看美劇】
本課程分成兩大部分。第一部分是每周以閱讀不同的主題來探討各國文化，例如: 音樂、節慶、食物等。同時對於學習評量，我們也將跳脫傳統的小考模式，改以讓同學報告他們有興趣的文化主題。第二部分老師在不同主題之間會加入美劇，讓同學觀賞並討論美國文化。

Theme of Course: Observing cultures through reading and watching American dramas

This course is designed into two parts. For the first part, students will learn different cultural knowledge and experience them through reading articles of different topics based on different cultures such as music, festivals, food and so on. Then, students will be given a topic and they have to present a culture they are interested.  The second part is watching American drama. Students will have a in-class discussion after watching  American drama."
4125,東海課程-大二英文大二英文：自我表達技巧(閔譯平老師1132-4125) ,閔譯平,必修課,0-2,LAN208,"[主題: 給初學者的課堂簡報課]
本課程的目的是幫助學生從基礎開始學習做簡報，大家會從「選擇適合的主題」以及「如何發想和組織報告的內容」開始。接下來學生也會學到一些技巧，讓自己在對著全班說話時比以前更有自信。這個課程沒有小考，而是讓同學們以完成各項作業或課後任務的分數為主。期中和期末成績的部分，則會以上台報告或同學製作的影片來評分。除此之外，大家也有機會和同學及老師用英文對話、互動。學生需使用英文錄影音檔案來完成課堂或課後作業。

[Course: Classroom presentation skills for beginners]
The aim of this course is to equip students with the fundamental skills necessary to deliver effective presentations. Initially, students will select an appropriate and engaging presentation topic and learn to structure their thoughts coherently. Subsequently, they will receive guidance on presentation techniques to enhance their confidence when speaking before an audience. Rather than traditional quizzes, students' grades will be based on their participation and completion of various in-class and after-class assignments. Both midterm and final assessments will involve delivering presentations or showing videos. Additionally, the course will offer opportunities for students to engage in English conversations with their classmates and the instructor. Students will also be required to submit audio and video recordings as part of their in-class and homework assignments."
4126,東海課程-大二英文大二英文：自我表達技巧(邱幸珍老師1132-4126) ,邱幸珍,必修課,0-2,LAN012,"The Mastery of Self Expression 說話達人
How do you get started to have a conversation? First, you need to know how to express yourself with confidence. Once you are confident, you will express yourself effectively. Before expressing yourself appropriately, there are some skills-- how to describe your feelings, how to depict an event, and how to motivate someone to listen to you, and even how to firmly speak out what you try to say. Let’s become a mastery of self-expression.
你如何開始重建對話關係？ 首先，您需要知道如何自信地表達自己。 一旦你有自信了，你就能有效地表達自己。在適當地表達自己之前，有一些技巧是需要掌握的——如何描述你的感受，如何描述一個事件，如何鼓勵別人聽你說話，甚至如何堅定地說出你想說的話。 讓我們成為自我表達的大師。"
4127,東海課程-大二英文大二英文：職涯與專業(黃怡瑋老師1132-4127) ,黃怡瑋,必修課,0-2,LAN005,"【主題: 職場英文攻略】:
此課程主要教授商用英文，課程內容包括英文履歷表與電子郵件的撰寫，以及英文自我介紹與面試等職場相關技能。望學生能夠應用所學，未來順利與職場接軌。

[Name: English Survival Skills for Workplaces]:
This course mainly teaches business English, as well as workplace-related skills such as writing English resumes, emails, self-introductions, and interviews. It is hoped that students can apply what they have learned and successfully integrate into the workplace in the future."
4128,東海課程-大二英文大二英文：職涯與專業(吳雨濃老師1132-4128) ,吳雨濃,必修課,0-2,A101,"【職涯與專業】
本課程旨英在專注於職場職業英語，教師教授語言發展的四項基本技能，強調聽力和口語。 由於這是一門職業和專業英語課程，因此將使用教科書和補充材料等材料強調熟悉這些學術和現實生活領域的背景，以便學生更有信心使用與職業相關的英語。

[Career and Profession] 
This course focuses on career and professional English for the workplace with the teacher teaching the four basic skills of language development emphasizing listening and speaking. As this is a career English course, the contexts familiar to both academic and real-life areas will be highlighted, using materials such as the textbook and supplemental materials. This approach aims to boost students' confidence in using career-related English."
4129,東海課程-大二英文大二英文：日常溝通(Amanda Parmley Wu老師1132-4129) ,Amanda Parmley Wu,必修課,0-2,LAN208,"**Find Your Voice (英語大聲公)**
你曾經花許多年來學英文，但卻仍害怕開口大聲說英文嗎？那麼，現在正是你來「英文大聲公」的時機！ 在這門課裡，你會發現一位充滿鼓勵的老師為你提供一個有安全感的環境來讓你用英文表達自己的想法。我們不會專注在學習新的單字與文法；不同的是，我們則是著重在讓你能夠使用你已經學過的單字，建立你的信心並能流暢地用英文來溝通。因此，來加入我們來找到你的英文大聲公。學習如何把你裡面的英文大聲說出來！
Have you spent years studying English but still get scared to open your mouth and speak English out loud? Then, it's time for you to FIND YOUR VOICE! In this speaking course, you'll find an encouraging teacher who offers a safe place for you to try to express your own ideas in English. We'll talk about relationships, food, life goals, and more. We won't focus on learning new vocabulary and grammar; instead, we'll focus on using what you already know, building confidence and fluency in your use of English for communicating. So, come join us and find your English voice. Come learn how to speak out what's inside!"
4130,東海課程-大二英文大二英文：日常溝通(Daniel Cothran老師1132-4130) ,Daniel Cothran,必修課,0-2,LAN014-1,"Communicating With People from Western Cultures英語通四海

This course aims to give students the language tools to communicate more effectively and comfortably in English with Westerners. Students will learn common expressions when talking about daily topics and discuss how culture plays an important role in choosing what and what not to talk about. Short reading and listening passages will introduce a topic and give students material to begin conversations. 

本課程的目標是為了提供語言工具，讓學生得以更有效更自在地使用英文和西方人士溝通。學生將學習到如何以常用語彙談論日常話題，以及在選定話題時文化所扮演的重要角色。短篇閱讀和聽力訓練也提供給學生一些對話的主題和素材."
4131,東海課程-大二英文大二英文：多元文化(劉怡芬老師1132-4131) ,劉怡芬,必修課,0-2,LAN015-1,"文化嘉年華
在這門課程中，學生將提升跨文化意識，培養對文化多樣性的更深層次理解。通過探索多樣的文化視角以及研究不同社會如何看待世界，學生將深入了解跨文化交流的奧秘。
課程將關注跨文化交流中的關鍵挑戰，例如刻板印象、誤解與曲解，並探討實用策略以促進在日益互聯的全球社會中的有效溝通。
加入我們，一起慶祝文化多樣性，拓寬視野，豐富全球化視角！
【Carnival of Cultures】
In this course, students will enhance their intercultural awareness and cultivate a deeper appreciation for cultural diversity. By exploring diverse cultural perspectives and examining how different societies perceive the world, students will gain valuable insights into intercultural communication.
The course addresses critical cross-cultural communication challenges, such as stereotyping, misinterpretations & misunderstandings, while offering practical strategies to promote effective communication in our increasingly interconnected global community.
Join us in celebrating cultural diversity, broadening your horizons, and enriching your global perspective!"
4132,東海課程-大二英文大二英文：多元文化(Stephanie Ruth Cothran老師1132-4132) ,Stephanie Ruth Cothran,必修課,0-2,LAN015,"主題：21世紀多元文化觀】
在本課程中，教師將透過各式創新有趣的教學活動，強化學生在21世紀應具備的英語能力及文化素養，帶領他們踏上探索世界文化傳統之旅。

[Name: Culture and Diversity in the 21st Century]
In this course, students will go on an exciting journey exploring different cultural traditions around the world. They will learn through different mediums and participate in fun classroom activities. They will also have the opportunity to hone their 21st century skills through creative and engaging task-based assignments."
4133,東海課程-大二英文大二英文：自我表達技巧(羅正佳老師1132-4133) ,羅正佳,必修課,0-2,A108,"Course Title: Building Confidence in English Presentations
